prompts.text:
To generate frames for animation:
-Set the prompts, models, loras, width, height and denoise
-Set the Keyframe interval (and loops)
-Set the Frames Cap
-Set the Frames Counter to 0 !!!
-Mute the Video combine group and other groups that are not in use*
-Set the output folder name (use unique names for every cycle)
-Check the Extra options in the Queue panel, then check Auto Queue (Comfy Manager required)
-Hit Queue
Don't use batch queue! Any batch leads to loading wrong temp latent in Receive latent node. That is what we have for now.**
When the generated images count reaches the Frames Cap value, an error will be displayed. This is the emergency brake... It means it's done.
The process can be paused at any time, by unchecking the Auto queue and then can be resumed. 

*Read the other notes on how to use Zoom in and ControlNet.

**There are some benefits: unlike any batch process, unlimited frames can be generated and some adjustments can be made during the generation. Uses less vram.

Use even numbers only.
The value means how many total pixels will be removed from the long side (the short side will be cropped proportionally).
To use Zoom out, enable it from Group Muter and set the switch to 2. Set it back to 1 (and mute the group) if not in use.
To use ControlNet, enable it from Group Muter and set the switch to 2. Set it back to 1 (and mute the group) if not in use.

To make a video from generated images, mute all other groups, upload it's folder, select the interpolation frames and set directory/names.
Don't forget to uncheck Auto Queue.

Use any ControlNet model (compatible with the checkpoint used). Connect Image Crop if needed.

To add more ControlNet:
-Extend the group
-Clone the essential nodes (in the group)
-Connect start in Image From Batch to the same input
-Connect positive and negative(before or after current node)
-Connect width and height if needed
-Optionally connect the load cap

Prompting is essential to achieve a good result:
-Write support words - e.g: if the ControlNet source images are for a dancing character, write "dancing (character)" in every keyframe row.
-Avoid drastic changes in neighboring keyframe prompts.

Recommended approx. denoise:
SD 1.5 models - from 6.7 to 7.3
SDXL models - from 7.5 to 8.5
but everything depends of the models used, loras and other settings.

Default value: 0.65 
Should be raised when using ControlNet.
Lower values will give smoother output, but requires to rise CFG and steps to avoid producing low quality images.

Default: fixed.
Use random for more dramatic changes.
Raise the CFG and steps (recommended) or denoise.
Connect Reverse Image Batch node to make a video from end to start. Can be useful to convert zoomed in images to zoomed out video.

Sometimes (after browser refresh, Comfy reload) latent file is changed to null and an error is popping up. To resolve this, just set it to undefined (and reset the counter).

- Latent is missing:
Check the Group mutter, ZoomIn and ControlNet switches, Latent Receiver, Link ID in Sender/Receiver, Frames counter

- Model is missing:
Check the Frames cap

- Too match tasks, after generating a video or CN preprocess:
Check the Auto Queue

- Images are not saved:
Check the Save image state
for testing purposes, set state to disabled.
